name: Das Boot
description:
Introduction

A short but fun canyon, best done in combination with The Subway. To do that you will need to reserve a permit for Das Boot and apply for the Subway lottery separately. When you go pick it up at the back country desk you will pay for one single permit.

Background

properties.name: R1 & R2 - Das Boot
properties.description: Rap 1 about 15 feet.  Rap 2 is about 8 feet.  When water levels are high one or more raps might not be present.

properties.name: Route Junction
properties.description: This spot is where the approaches for Russell Gulch and Das Boot intersect the main Left Fork route.  It is unmarked and may not be obvious.

properties.name: Trail Junction
properties.description: On approach, leave the Wildcat Canyon trail and take the Northgate Peaks trail.  This may, or may not be signed.  More than a few groups have missed this turn.  Reverse on exit.

properties.name: Informal Trail
properties.description: After walking on the Northgate Peaks trail for a very short while, depart the trail down an obvious use path.  This is the start of the Left Fork (Subway) Approach.  There is much trail damage so try to minimize impact.  Follow the most used route. Reverse on exit.

properties.name: Subway Exit - Additional Permit Required
properties.description: It is possible to exit via the Subway but an additional permit is required.  If exiting this way see the RopeWiki page for the Subway for route info and GPX tracks.
